Arrays in Java are Reference Types
Array variable stores address, not actual data.
Arrays are Passed by Reference
When array is sent to a function, original array is passed.
Changes in Function Affect Original Array
Modification inside method = modification in main array.
Assignment Does NOT Create Copy
Java
Copy code
int[] b = a;
a and b point to same array.
Need for Real Copy
Direct assignment is NOT independent copy.
Correct Ways to Copy Array
Manual loop copy
clone() method
Java
Copy code
int[] b = a.clone();
Returning Array from Function is Allowed
Functions can return whole array.
Side Effect Concept
Passing array can unintentionally modify original data.
Primitive vs Array Difference
Primitive â†’ pass by value
Array â†’ pass by reference
Key Takeaway
Always be careful when modifying arrays inside functions.




   
